reviews.review_text:
interesting pa mix bobby way out front and jerry in the distance. it's almost as if the motb part of this recording relates to how prominent bobby's guitar is as the rest sounds like the typical boomyness of winterland - rather distant vocals too.

that said it's still a solid aud recording for the era esp after settling into its overall sound - it's rather nice. super laid back scarlet > fire, almost meditative transition.

thanks for all the great sound work and getting these recordings out there mixers, uploaders etc.
